                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.5151/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-06T21:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 6, 1943—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 8—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2249. From Landis<note n="12" xml:id="d982fn12">James M. Landis, American
                        Director of Economic Operations in the Middle East and principal American
                        civilian representative at the Middle East Supply Center, Cairo.</note> and
                    Moose.</p>
                <p>“We strongly feel that action should be taken on proposed currency scheme for
                    Saudi Arabia. Eastern Bank recently requested permission to open a branch in
                    Eastern Saudi Arabia. Establishment of British Bank might result in increasing
                    British financial control and assumption of functions which ought to be
                    performed by financial situation in which there is American participation.
                    Treasury has been furnished with background material by its representatives in
                    Cairo.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
